1. lsblk
Use: Displays block devices (disks, partitions, LVM) in a tree format.
Why used: To identify attached disks and partitions.

2. df
Use: Shows disk space usage of mounted file systems.
Why used: To check available and used disk space.
df -h

3. du
Use: Displays disk usage of files and directories.
Why used: To find which directory is consuming more space.
du -sh /var/log

4. mount
Use: Mounts a filesystem to a directory.
Why used: To make a disk/partition accessible.
mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt

5. umount
Use: Unmounts a filesystem.
Why used: Before removing a disk safely.
umount /mnt

6. blkid
Use: Displays UUID and filesystem type of block devices.
Why used: Required for permanent mounting using /etc/fstab.
blkid

7. fdisk
Use: Creates, deletes, and manages disk partitions (MBR).
Why used: Partitioning new disks.
fdisk /dev/sdb
